\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 18.         Micropus}          L.
\par 

\pard\f0\fs24\qc By J. Holub.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28 Like{\i  Bombycilaena} but sericeous-tomentose; leaves opposite, widest near the apex; capitula solitary in the leaf-axils; bracts in 2 rows, the outer small, the inner saccate, connate at the base, crested on the keel.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. M. supinus} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 927 (1753). Stem 2-20 cm, procumbent or ascending, rigid. Leaves 12-20 × 4-11 mm, oblong-obovate to obovate-spathulate, rounded to subacute at apex, flat. Capitula 5-7 mm wide. Outer bracts 1-1·2 mm, membranous, the inner 4-5, 5-8 mm in fruit, densely appressed-hairy. Female florets 4-5; hermaphrodite florets purplish, glabrous above. Achenes 2·3-2·5 × 1-1·3 mm, obliquely obovoid, pale brown, glabrous, shining. {\i Dry, open habitats. C. & S. Spain, S.E. Portugal; casual elsewhere in the Mediterranean region.} Hs Lu.
\par 

