\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. O. sylvatica} (L.) Schultz Bip. & F. W. Schultz in F. W. Schultz, {\i Arch. Fl. Jour. Bot.} 311 (1861) ({\i Gnaphalium sylvaticum} L.). Plant greyish-sericeous-tomentose, with several non-flowering shoots. Stem (5-)20-50(-70) cm, densely leafy. Leaves 2-8 × 0·2-0·8 cm, lanceolate to linear, 1 (or indistinctly 3)-veined, diminishing steadily in size up the stem, tomentose beneath, glabrescent above, erecto-patent. Inflorescence occupying 1/3-5/6 of the length of the stem, lax, interrupted below. Capitula 5-7 × 1·5-2 mm. Involucral bracts 5-5·5 mm, linear-oblong, the inner about equalling the florets. Florets 3·5 mm, the female c. 70, the hermaphrodite 3-4. Achenes 1·5 mm, hispid; pappus 3·5-3·8 mm, reddish. 2n = 56.{\i  Open woods, heaths and grassland; somewhat calcifuge. Most of Europe except many of the islands}. Al Au Be Br Bu Co Cz Da Fe Ga Ge Gr Hb He Ho Hs Hu Is It Ju No Po Rm Rs (N, B, C, W, K, E) Su.
